</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[146,1103,209,1142]" box="[146,787,209,233]" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">
Body length 
<quantity box="[295,356,209,233]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="406" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
(female), wing length 
<quantity box="[616,678,209,233]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="406" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
(female).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[146,1103,209,1142]" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[268,416,242,266]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[213,280,1625,1647]" captionTargetBox="[215,1168,712,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-62@7.[213,1171,710,1588]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Platycephala lateralis sp. nov. (female): (A) head, dorsal view; (B) head, lateral view; (C) hind femur and tibia, anterior view; (D) antenna, lateral view; (E) abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; (F) abdominal terminalia, ventral view. Scale bar 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5218410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5218410/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">Figure 3Aâ€“B</figureCitation>
) brown, triangular in profile, about 1.5 times longer than high; frons not strongly produced beyond anterior level of eye, in profile about 0.35 times as long as long axis of eye; gena prominently broadened posterad, anteriorly strongly narrowed below eye; parafacial about 0.028 times as long as long axis of eye. Frontal triangle trapezoid, occupying most area of frons, reaching its anterior margin and semicircular anteriorly with blackish lateral margin; ocellar triangle and surrounding area black; area between eye and frontal triangle depressed and brown-yellow. Setulae and setae on head brown. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[883,998,469,493]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[213,280,1625,1647]" captionTargetBox="[215,1168,712,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-62@7.[213,1171,710,1588]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Platycephala lateralis sp. nov. (female): (A) head, dorsal view; (B) head, lateral view; (C) hind femur and tibia, anterior view; (D) antenna, lateral view; (E) abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; (F) abdominal terminalia, ventral view. Scale bar 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5218410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5218410/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">Figure 3C</figureCitation>
) brown; pedicel blackish, 0.6 times as long as third antennal segment; third antennal segment nearly rectangular, 1.7 times longer than wide, rounded apically; arista pale yellow, pale short pubescent. Proboscis and palpus pale yellow with pale setulae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[146,1103,209,1142]" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">
Thorax black, slightly narrower than head; anterior portion of humerus brown, propleuron brown with a black spot, upper portion of anepimeron yellow; mesonotum 1.1 times longer than wide, with prominent setigerous punctures; scutellum 1.5 times wider than long. Setulae and setae on thorax black; katepisternum with some long thin setulae. Legs brown; hind femur (
<figureCitation box="[978,1093,761,785]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[213,280,1625,1647]" captionTargetBox="[215,1168,712,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-62@7.[213,1171,710,1588]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Platycephala lateralis sp. nov. (female): (A) head, dorsal view; (B) head, lateral view; (C) hind femur and tibia, anterior view; (D) antenna, lateral view; (E) abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; (F) abdominal terminalia, ventral view. Scale bar 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5218410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5218410/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">Figure 3D</figureCitation>
) and hind tibia with blackish area, and hind femur with a distinct black stripe on apical portion; hind femur thickened, about 3.8 times longer than wide and 2.1 times thicker than fore femur; hind tibia somewhat curved. Setulae on legs pale; hind femur with some long setulae. Wing hyaline; veins mostly brown. Relative lengths of costal sections second:third:fourth55.5:7.9:5.5. Squama yellow with pale setulae. Halter blackish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[146,1103,209,1142]" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">
Abdomen blackish, light microtrichose; dorsum slightly rugose; venter brown. Setulae and setae on abdomen black. Genitalia (
<specimenCount box="[727,741,1024,1044]" pageId="8" pageNumber="406" type="female">â™€</specimenCount>
) (
<figureCitation box="[769,916,1021,1045]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[213,280,1625,1647]" captionTargetBox="[215,1168,712,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-62@7.[213,1171,710,1588]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Platycephala lateralis sp. nov. (female): (A) head, dorsal view; (B) head, lateral view; (C) hind femur and tibia, anterior view; (D) antenna, lateral view; (E) abdominal terminalia, dorsal view; (F) abdominal terminalia, ventral view. Scale bar 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5218410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5218410/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">Figure 3Eâ€“F</figureCitation>
): brown-yellow; tergite 8 semicircular; sternite 8 separated at middle; sternite 9 subtriangular; cerci stout. Setulae on genitalia brown; tergite 9 with one pair of long setulae; tergite 8 with one row of long setulae on apical margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[146,280,1218,1242]" box="[146,280,1218,1242]" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">
<emphasis box="[146,280,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
