<collectingCountry box="[146,215,1258,1282]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[232,373,1258,1282]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[146,267,1339,1363]" box="[146,267,1339,1363]" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">
<emphasis box="[146,267,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[146,1103,1380,1436]" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">
The Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="An &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2009" box="[266,355,1380,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Platycephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateralis">
<emphasis box="[266,355,1380,1404]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">lateralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
means lateral. The species is named after the black lateral margin of the frontal triangle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[146,245,1512,1536]" box="[146,245,1512,1536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">
<emphasis box="[146,245,1512,1536]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[146,1103,1553,1706]" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="An and Yang" authorityName="An and Yang" box="[497,846,1553,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Platycephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lii">
<emphasis box="[497,674,1553,1577]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">Platycephala lii</emphasis>
An and Yang
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[924,1023,1553,1577]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
in the elongate and narrowed frontal triangle, and the black lateral margin of the frontal triangle, but can be separated from the latter by the distinct parafacial and the hind femur with a distinct black stripe. In 
<taxonomicName box="[569,623,1650,1674]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Platycephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lii">
<emphasis box="[569,623,1650,1674]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="406">P. lii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the parafacial is distinctly narrowed, and the hind femur is only tinged with some black (
<bibRefCitation author="An S &amp; Yang D" box="[695,918,1682,1706]" pageId="8" pageNumber="406" pagination="651 - 656" refId="ref4075" refString="An S, Yang D. 2003. A review of the genus Platycephala Fallen, 1820 from China (Diptera: Chloropidae). Ann Zool. 53 (4): 651 - 656." type="journal article" year="2003">An and Yang 2003</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
